00:02:32.900 --> 00:02:35.190
And she was wonderful.

00:02:35.190 --> 00:02:36.290
And you were there.

00:02:36.290 --> 00:02:39.040
We had a very feisty
conversation about it.

00:02:39.040 --> 00:02:40.160
And I'm a big fan of hers.

00:02:40.160 --> 00:02:44.120
But that day I thought to
myself, as she was speaking,

00:02:44.120 --> 00:02:46.430
I thought, who's going
to tell our stories?

00:02:46.430 --> 00:02:49.250
Who's going to tell the
stories of women like us

00:02:49.250 --> 00:02:51.820
that are immigrants or
the kids of immigrants

00:02:51.820 --> 00:02:54.140
or who have had
detours or women that

00:02:54.140 --> 00:02:57.830
are Muslim or
African-American or Asian,

00:02:57.830 --> 00:03:00.770
who really come to this
country and reinvent themselves

00:03:00.770 --> 00:03:03.180
and are emerging in
countries around the world?

00:03:03.180 --> 00:03:05.580
And I heard in my ear,
you do it, you do it.

00:03:05.580 --> 00:03:08.270
And then, of course,
sometimes our low self-esteem

00:03:08.270 --> 00:03:10.070
shows up and goes,
[SPEAKING SPANISH],,

00:03:10.070 --> 00:03:11.870
what do you think you are?

00:03:11.870 --> 00:03:15.320
And then I said, if you don't
do it, who is going to do it?

00:03:15.320 --> 00:03:17.750
And I did it, and I'm
very proud that I've

00:03:17.750 --> 00:03:21.950
spent a year, 140 cities
around the country,

00:03:21.950 --> 00:03:24.890
meeting all kinds of
women and really uniting

00:03:24.890 --> 00:03:29.150
with not just all multicultural
women but with white women.

00:03:29.150 --> 00:03:31.580
And we now know after
the whole election

00:03:31.580 --> 00:03:34.130
that this is an incredible
year for all of us

00:03:34.130 --> 00:03:36.040
and that we need to
talk about this issue.

00:03:36.040 --> 00:03:37.400
SPEAKER 1: We have
power, a lot of power.

00:03:37.400 --> 00:03:39.710
NELY GALAN: A lot of power,
power that we don't even

00:03:39.710 --> 00:03:41.180
know we have.

00:03:41.180 --> 00:03:43.250
SPEAKER 1: Now tell us,
what is "Self Made?"

00:03:43.250 --> 00:03:44.870
What does it mean
to be Self Made?

00:03:44.870 --> 00:03:46.280
NELY GALAN: So
"Self Made," it so

00:03:46.280 --> 00:03:47.896
wonderful to be
in a tech company

00:03:47.896 --> 00:03:50.270
and talk about "Self Made"
because it doesn't mean you're

00:03:50.270 --> 00:03:53.510
going to leave your job and go
be an entrepreneur tomorrow.

00:03:53.510 --> 00:03:57.050
It also doesn't mean, especially
all of you in Silicon Valley,

00:03:57.050 --> 00:04:00.980
that one of you is going to go
off and be the next Zuckerberg.

00:04:00.980 --> 00:04:04.010
These are one-in-a-million
situations.

00:04:04.010 --> 00:04:07.370
But the good news is
Self Made is a mindset.

00:04:07.370 --> 00:04:12.272
It begins by thinking like
an owner in what you do now.

00:04:12.272 --> 00:04:13.730
You're not going
to leave your job.

00:04:13.730 --> 00:04:16.313
You're going to think every day
that you're in business school

00:04:16.313 --> 00:04:19.040
working for other people,
using other people's money,

00:04:19.040 --> 00:04:20.839
and sitting there
every day and saying,

00:04:20.839 --> 00:04:23.630
if this were my company,
what would I do?

00:04:23.630 --> 00:04:25.310
Would I spend this money?

00:04:25.310 --> 00:04:28.670
And make sure that you let
your bosses know how you feel.

00:04:28.670 --> 00:04:32.480
You're practicing being
a founder and an owner.

00:04:32.480 --> 00:04:34.610
And if they don't listen
to you, that's fine.

00:04:34.610 --> 00:04:37.670
But you have to, every day,
come into work not thinking

00:04:37.670 --> 00:04:39.980
victimized, thinking
like an owner.

00:04:39.980 --> 00:04:44.780
The future for all of us is to
think and behave like owners.

00:04:44.780 --> 00:04:49.250
Then we have to think that
Self Made is a mindset.

00:04:49.250 --> 00:04:51.650
And it's a mindset
of understanding

00:04:51.650 --> 00:04:54.170
that the United States works
on a premise that most of us

00:04:54.170 --> 00:04:55.100
don't know.

00:04:55.100 --> 00:04:58.260
The premise is that, to make
it to the end of your life,

00:04:58.260 --> 00:05:01.310
you have to make
money while you sleep,

00:05:01.310 --> 00:05:04.280
which one of my billionaire
bosses and mentors

00:05:04.280 --> 00:05:07.100
told me that, I was like it
sounds like a foreign language.

00:05:07.100 --> 00:05:08.660
I didn't even know
what that meant.

00:05:08.660 --> 00:05:11.975
That meant that the money
you make at whatever job

00:05:11.975 --> 00:05:13.850
you do, whether you work
here, whether you're

00:05:13.850 --> 00:05:16.772
a doctor or a lawyer, if
you just count on the money

00:05:16.772 --> 00:05:18.230
you make and money
you save, you're

00:05:18.230 --> 00:05:20.390
not going to make it to
the end of your life.

00:05:20.390 --> 00:05:24.350
So entrepreneurship isn't just
becoming a founder or a maker.

00:05:24.350 --> 00:05:27.290
It's also being someone that
makes money, saves money.

00:05:27.290 --> 00:05:30.350
Sometimes you have to do it
by starting a side hustle.

00:05:30.350 --> 00:05:34.310
And that money you save you
have to invest in, like me,

00:05:34.310 --> 00:05:35.840
real estate, which
we'll talk about.

00:05:35.840 --> 00:05:38.060
That why I say, don't
buy shoes, buy buildings.

00:05:38.060 --> 00:05:39.890
Or invest it in stock.

00:05:39.890 --> 00:05:42.260
Or invest it in buying
an existing business

00:05:42.260 --> 00:05:45.220
and let other people run
it while you have job.

00:05:45.220 --> 00:05:48.250
Or supplier diversity,
where you understand

00:05:48.250 --> 00:05:51.040
that there's a lot of
contracts in corporations

00:05:51.040 --> 00:05:54.100
and in the government
that are earmarked

00:05:54.100 --> 00:05:57.280
for women particularly
and multicultural women

00:05:57.280 --> 00:05:58.541
specifically.

00:05:58.541 --> 00:06:00.040
And guys, if you
want to make money,

00:06:00.040 --> 00:06:02.770
partner with a woman and a
multicultural woman and you'll

00:06:02.770 --> 00:06:04.180
do better.

00:06:04.180 --> 00:06:07.090
That we understand that, whether
you're an entrepreneur that

00:06:07.090 --> 00:06:11.650
leaves your company or not, you
must think entrepreneurially

00:06:11.650 --> 00:06:15.040
from this moment on in
your life to make it.

00:06:15.040 --> 00:06:19.219
SPEAKER 1: Tell us tell
us about Nely at age 12.

00:06:19.219 --> 00:06:20.260
Where did this come from?

00:06:20.260 --> 00:06:21.610
When did you become Self Made?

00:06:21.610 --> 00:06:24.710
When did you get this
entrepreneurial spirit?

00:06:24.710 --> 00:06:27.400
NELY GALAN: I think for me, it
all began in the seventh grade.

00:06:27.400 --> 00:06:29.830
I think for so many
of us sometimes

00:06:29.830 --> 00:06:32.170
our greatness comes from pain.

00:06:32.170 --> 00:06:33.910
I was the kid of immigrants.

00:06:33.910 --> 00:06:34.690
We had no money.

00:06:34.690 --> 00:06:37.120
My parents came
from communist Cuba.

00:06:37.120 --> 00:06:39.130
They lost everything,
including their degrees.

00:06:39.130 --> 00:06:40.840
They had to start all over.

00:06:40.840 --> 00:06:42.390
I became the hero child.

00:06:42.390 --> 00:06:45.550
I had to help them translate
for them, do everything.

00:06:45.550 --> 00:06:50.030
And in the seventh grade, we
were having a lot of struggles

00:06:50.030 --> 00:06:50.980
financially.

00:06:50.980 --> 00:06:53.470
I was in all-girl
Catholic school.

00:06:53.470 --> 00:06:57.370
And basically, I would
overhear my parents saying,

00:06:57.370 --> 00:06:58.616
what are we going to do?

00:06:58.616 --> 00:07:00.490
What are we going to
do, my father would say.

00:07:00.490 --> 00:07:02.650
And my mother would
say, [SPEAKING SPANISH]..

00:07:02.650 --> 00:07:04.270
And my dad would
say, don't worry.

00:07:04.270 --> 00:07:06.400
Jesus will help us.

00:07:06.400 --> 00:07:10.240
And I realized that I had
to go help my parents out.

00:07:10.240 --> 00:07:13.360
And a lady down the street, an
older Jewish lady, sold Avon.

00:07:13.360 --> 00:07:14.860
And she's like,
honey, why don't you

00:07:14.860 --> 00:07:17.370
sell Avon and you get
some free lipstick?

00:07:17.370 --> 00:07:19.630
I go, I got to
cut a better deal.

00:07:19.630 --> 00:07:22.810
And I went and said to her,
I will sell Avon in school,

00:07:22.810 --> 00:07:25.300
but I need it to be 50-50.

00:07:25.300 --> 00:07:29.860
And I started making money,
$200 a week selling Avon,

00:07:29.860 --> 00:07:35.020
paying down my entire
tuition, and then

00:07:35.020 --> 00:07:37.840
having the nuns send home
a letter to my parents

00:07:37.840 --> 00:07:41.240
so my dad wouldn't be upset that
I was paying down the tuition.

00:07:41.240 --> 00:07:43.760
And I brought it home and my
mother goes, what does it say?

00:07:43.760 --> 00:07:46.900
And my father goes, your
daughter is a genius

00:07:46.900 --> 00:07:50.080
and Jesus helped us after all.

00:07:50.080 --> 00:07:53.440
And I think that was the
beginning of the aha.

00:07:53.440 --> 00:07:56.170
That, if there is a
problem, we can fix it.

00:07:56.170 --> 00:07:57.700
There's no point
in being a victim.

00:07:57.700 --> 00:07:59.420
We fix it.

00:07:59.420 --> 00:08:01.420
And I think that
life is a series

00:08:01.420 --> 00:08:06.400
of those issues that, maybe for
someone else, is a catastrophe.

00:08:06.400 --> 00:08:11.230
And for me, it was like the
beginning blocks of my-- you

00:08:11.230 --> 00:08:14.140
know when Beyonce talks
about her persona,

00:08:14.140 --> 00:08:20.050
Sasha Fierce I am a Latina
immigrant from New Jersey who's

00:08:20.050 --> 00:08:24.400
sometimes has self-esteem issues
show up and I don't feel good,

00:08:24.400 --> 00:08:26.370
and then I created a persona.

00:08:26.370 --> 00:08:30.040
And I got my own version
of Sasha Fierce going on.

00:08:30.040 --> 00:08:31.660
I'm a beast.

00:08:31.660 --> 00:08:34.240
And it happened
brick by brick, step

00:08:34.240 --> 00:08:39.159
by step, learning that no
one else is smarter than us,

00:08:39.159 --> 00:08:42.730
that it's a matter of
being louder and braver.

00:08:42.730 --> 00:08:45.700
This is not a country
of wimpy people.

00:08:45.700 --> 00:08:48.610
This is not a country
of not understanding

00:08:48.610 --> 00:08:50.950
the Constitution and
the First Amendment

00:08:50.950 --> 00:08:54.010
and not understanding
that you have rights

00:08:54.010 --> 00:08:56.977
and that we're all very
much part of this country

00:08:56.977 --> 00:08:58.310
and our voice needs to be heard.

00:08:58.310 --> 00:09:00.070
I mean, don't you
love seeing a Latina

00:09:00.070 --> 00:09:04.240
on mainstream TV defending
women, multicultural women

00:09:04.240 --> 00:09:05.080
and Latinas?

00:09:05.080 --> 00:09:07.730
Why do we feel like
we can't do that?

00:09:07.730 --> 00:09:11.500
Why do we marginalize
ourselves in small situations

00:09:11.500 --> 00:09:14.260
when in fact we have all
the power in the world.

00:09:14.260 --> 00:09:17.410
Latinas in this country are
the number one emerging market.

00:09:17.410 --> 00:09:19.630
That means we are the
number one consumers

00:09:19.630 --> 00:09:22.790
in America, together with
African-American women,

00:09:22.790 --> 00:09:25.360
Asian women, Middle
Eastern women.

00:09:25.360 --> 00:09:28.210
If we unite together,
there is no company

00:09:28.210 --> 00:09:30.730
that can survive without us.

00:09:30.730 --> 00:09:35.620
So how do we not put that
information inside our bodies

00:09:35.620 --> 00:09:37.990
and become empowered
and know that we have

00:09:37.990 --> 00:09:39.130
all the power in the world.

00:09:39.130 --> 00:09:39.970
SPEAKER 1: We take ownership.

00:09:39.970 --> 00:09:40.855
We are Self Made.

00:09:40.855 --> 00:09:42.480
It's a mentality,
changing the mindset.

00:09:42.480 --> 00:09:43.521
NELY GALAN: That's right.

00:09:43.521 --> 00:09:44.440
It's a mindset shift.

00:09:44.440 --> 00:09:46.660
SPEAKER 1: Now, there is
a moment in your journey

00:09:46.660 --> 00:09:48.874
when you were working
for a corporation.

00:09:48.874 --> 00:09:49.540
NELY GALAN: Yes.

00:09:49.540 --> 00:09:51.790
SPEAKER 1: And you
realized at that moment

00:09:51.790 --> 00:09:53.960
that you were
acting like an owner

00:09:53.960 --> 00:09:56.020
but you really weren't an owner.

00:09:56.020 --> 00:09:57.400
Can you tell us a little bit?

00:09:57.400 --> 00:10:00.910
NELY GALAN: So I got into
television very early on.

00:10:00.910 --> 00:10:04.024
I was lucky because I wrote an
article to "Seventeen" magazine

00:10:04.024 --> 00:10:05.690
about why you should
never send your kid

00:10:05.690 --> 00:10:09.652
to all-girl Catholic school,
and they published it.

00:10:09.652 --> 00:10:11.110
And it was a big
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

00:10:11.110 --> 00:10:12.550
in my family.

00:10:12.550 --> 00:10:15.040
And as a result,
"Seventeen" magazine

00:10:15.040 --> 00:10:19.432
offered me the youngest guest
editorship in their history.

00:10:19.432 --> 00:10:21.890
So again, that's when I learned
it doesn't pay to be wimpy.

00:10:21.890 --> 00:10:23.380
Speak up.

00:10:23.380 --> 00:10:25.150
And I got into
"Seventeen" magazine,

00:10:25.150 --> 00:10:28.180
which led me to television,
which in my wildest

00:10:28.180 --> 00:10:30.280
dreams I would never have done.

00:10:30.280 --> 00:10:34.510
And very early on,
in television I

00:10:34.510 --> 00:10:36.430
was interviewing
a lot of people,

00:10:36.430 --> 00:10:40.300
and I met a gentleman who was a
very big producer in Hollywood.

00:10:40.300 --> 00:10:41.950
And he's like, are you Latina?

00:10:41.950 --> 00:10:42.550
What are you?

00:10:42.550 --> 00:10:44.130
And I said, yeah, I am.

00:10:44.130 --> 00:10:47.360
And he said, I just bought
the first Spanish TV station

00:10:47.360 --> 00:10:48.930
in America.

00:10:48.930 --> 00:10:51.110
And he's like, why don't
you come and work for me?

00:10:51.110 --> 00:10:52.040
And I go, excuse me.

00:10:52.040 --> 00:10:53.690
I work for CBS.

00:10:53.690 --> 00:10:58.070
Why do I want to work for some
rinky-dinky Spanish TV station?

00:10:58.070 --> 00:10:59.500
And he's like, I'm rich.

00:10:59.500 --> 00:11:00.950
Are you rich?

00:11:00.950 --> 00:11:02.930
He goes, young
lady, what would it

00:11:02.930 --> 00:11:06.200
mean to be employee one of a
business that's going to be

00:11:06.200 --> 00:11:08.000
a multibillion dollar business?

00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:10.250
And I was like, oh
my god, he sounds

00:11:10.250 --> 00:11:12.130
a little smarter than me.

00:11:12.130 --> 00:11:16.970
And I think that was my first
attempt at not really thinking

00:11:16.970 --> 00:11:19.540
any more about what
is my career path,

00:11:19.540 --> 00:11:22.310
but who are the people
that I'm going to follow

00:11:22.310 --> 00:11:24.570
that are smarter than me?

00:11:24.570 --> 00:11:27.640
I went and at 22
years of age ran,

00:11:27.640 --> 00:11:28.880
I was the general manager--

00:11:28.880 --> 00:11:30.840
the youngest general
manager in the country--

00:11:30.840 --> 00:11:33.170
of the first Latino
TV station, which

00:11:33.170 --> 00:11:36.380
is now Telemundo but back then
it was an independent station.

00:11:36.380 --> 00:11:37.850
I killed myself.

00:11:37.850 --> 00:11:39.680
I thought like an owner.

00:11:39.680 --> 00:11:41.160
I worked 24 hours a day.

00:11:41.160 --> 00:11:42.466
I had no personal life.

00:11:42.466 --> 00:11:44.090
And three years later,
I walk into work

00:11:44.090 --> 00:11:46.327
and they had sold the company.

00:11:46.327 --> 00:11:47.910
And I went to see
my boss, and I said,

00:11:47.910 --> 00:11:49.760
how could you do this to me?

00:11:49.760 --> 00:11:51.370
This is my baby.

00:11:51.370 --> 00:11:53.150
And I'm crying and
bawling, everything

00:11:53.150 --> 00:11:54.390
they tell you not to do.

00:11:54.390 --> 00:11:56.870
And he's like, stop, young lady.

00:11:56.870 --> 00:11:58.590
Those are my chips.

00:11:58.590 --> 00:12:02.360
If you want to play,
go get your own chips.

00:12:02.360 --> 00:12:05.480
And that is the
moment I had to mourn

00:12:05.480 --> 00:12:07.460
that I was losing
my baby, and then I

00:12:07.460 --> 00:12:10.010
said I have to start
my own business.

00:12:10.010 --> 00:12:14.270
And so I started a business
at 25 making TV shows,

00:12:14.270 --> 00:12:16.430
or that's what I thought
I was going to do.

00:12:16.430 --> 00:12:18.850
And for four years, I
did not make a penny.

00:12:21.730 --> 00:12:22.980
I would tell you the opposite.

00:12:22.980 --> 00:12:24.690
Do not leave your job.

00:12:24.690 --> 00:12:26.910
Don't just go bootstrapping
without knowing

00:12:26.910 --> 00:12:28.140
what you're going to do.

00:12:28.140 --> 00:12:30.906
I have a whole formula
for you, but I did that.

00:12:30.906 --> 00:12:32.530
And can you imagine
the Latino parents?

00:12:32.530 --> 00:12:34.500
Por favor, find the husband.

00:12:34.500 --> 00:12:37.410
You're losing your looks.

00:12:37.410 --> 00:12:41.850
And four years later, I
was like praying to God.

00:12:41.850 --> 00:12:44.940
Dear God, por favor,
throw me a bone.

00:12:44.940 --> 00:12:46.410
Everybody thinks I'm a loser.

00:12:46.410 --> 00:12:48.900
It was not cool to be
an entrepreneur then.

00:12:48.900 --> 00:12:51.510
All my friends were like,
dude, can you get a job?

00:12:51.510 --> 00:12:53.310
What's your problem?

00:12:53.310 --> 00:12:55.110
And in the fourth
year, I got invited

00:12:55.110 --> 00:12:57.870
to a Chamber of Commerce event.

00:12:57.870 --> 00:12:59.280
And I went.

00:12:59.280 --> 00:13:01.200
And I always say, in
life, if you show up,

00:13:01.200 --> 00:13:03.430
maybe something happens,
maybe nothing happens.

00:13:03.430 --> 00:13:06.660
But if you don't show up,
nothing happens-- guaranteed.

00:13:06.660 --> 00:13:09.090
I went, and I started
asking people,

00:13:09.090 --> 00:13:11.310
what's wrong with
my business plan?

00:13:11.310 --> 00:13:14.370
And they said immediately,
they were like, your business

00:13:14.370 --> 00:13:16.600
plan is wrong.

00:13:16.600 --> 00:13:19.140
There is no pipeline
for your content.

00:13:19.140 --> 00:13:20.820
There's only one station.

00:13:20.820 --> 00:13:24.310
You need to go build the
pipeline and the distribution.

00:13:24.310 --> 00:13:28.260
So I switched my business
plan to launching TV channels

00:13:28.260 --> 00:13:30.490
around the world
for big companies.

00:13:30.490 --> 00:13:32.670
So it was supplier
diversity in a way.

00:13:32.670 --> 00:13:40.050
So I basically went to work
with Fox, HBO, ESPN, Sony,

00:13:40.050 --> 00:13:42.720
and I would take their brand
and launch it in Latin America.

00:13:42.720 --> 00:13:43.620
SPEAKER 1: And they would fund?

00:13:43.620 --> 00:13:44.280
NELY GALAN: They would fund it.

00:13:44.280 --> 00:13:45.230
It was my business.

00:13:45.230 --> 00:13:48.360
So if it screwed up, they
could get rid of me easily.

00:13:48.360 --> 00:13:49.380
It was my own business.

00:13:49.380 --> 00:13:51.930
And then I launched
it separately,

00:13:51.930 --> 00:13:54.120
and I launched 10
channels that way.

00:13:54.120 --> 00:13:57.990
And then the original
TV station that I ran

00:13:57.990 --> 00:14:00.690
was bought by an American
insurance company,

00:14:00.690 --> 00:14:02.520
and they had bought
a bunch of stations.

00:14:02.520 --> 00:14:04.980
And they didn't know how
to run a Latino network.

00:14:04.980 --> 00:14:06.330
So it went into bankruptcy.

00:14:06.330 --> 00:14:07.740
Sony bought it.

00:14:07.740 --> 00:14:09.660
Sony was my client.

00:14:09.660 --> 00:14:12.100
I had launched their
channels abroad.

00:14:12.100 --> 00:14:13.740
And I was the only
Latina that they

00:14:13.740 --> 00:14:16.860
knew that had fiscal
responsibility

00:14:16.860 --> 00:14:19.900
for large entities
of theirs abroad.

00:14:19.900 --> 00:14:22.830
And so they basically
offered to buy my business

00:14:22.830 --> 00:14:25.390
and offered me the
presidency of entertainment,

00:14:25.390 --> 00:14:27.190
which is running the network.

00:14:27.190 --> 00:14:30.127
That's the creative
job in a network.

00:14:30.127 --> 00:14:31.710
And so I ran Telemundo
for four years,

00:14:31.710 --> 00:14:33.840
and I went back
into corporate life.

00:14:33.840 --> 00:14:36.940
So I understand
very much becoming

00:14:36.940 --> 00:14:40.500
Self Made as an
intraentrepreneur

00:14:40.500 --> 00:14:43.560
and as an entrepreneur
outside of a corporation.

00:14:43.560 --> 00:14:47.310
And both ways is very important
because only in a corporation

00:14:47.310 --> 00:14:49.205
do you learn how
to scale something.

00:14:49.205 --> 00:14:49.830
SPEAKER 1: Yes.

00:14:49.830 --> 00:14:51.204
I think we are
all learning that.

00:14:51.204 --> 00:14:53.460
I think even myself.

00:14:53.460 --> 00:14:56.130
Myself and Iliana who's
here have coined ourselves

00:14:56.130 --> 00:14:59.880
as the intrapreneurs, creating
and seeing opportunities

00:14:59.880 --> 00:15:01.070
where they don't exist.

00:15:01.070 --> 00:15:04.380
Now, tell me, so you mentioned
your mom at one point

00:15:04.380 --> 00:15:07.050
and your parents were
saying, andale, you

00:15:07.050 --> 00:15:07.980
need to get a husband.

00:15:07.980 --> 00:15:10.200
And you mentioned in
your book that there's

00:15:10.200 --> 00:15:14.220
no such thing as Prince
Charming or Princess Charming.

00:15:14.220 --> 00:15:16.410
NELY GALAN: Well, I
think it is a bigger

00:15:16.410 --> 00:15:19.620
idea than even how I say it.

00:15:19.620 --> 00:15:21.270
I say there is no
Prince Charming,

00:15:21.270 --> 00:15:23.880
and I don't mean that
against guys or anything.

00:15:23.880 --> 00:15:26.490
I think there's no Prince
Charming for any of us.

00:15:26.490 --> 00:15:33.210
I think the idea that a mate
or a boss or a corporation

00:15:33.210 --> 00:15:38.610
or a government or a president
is here to save us is false.

00:15:38.610 --> 00:15:42.540
I think that, when you work for
other people, you often think,

00:15:42.540 --> 00:15:44.760
whether you're a man
or woman, my boss

00:15:44.760 --> 00:15:47.900
is going to see how great I am
and give me the big promotion.

00:15:47.900 --> 00:15:50.640
And your boss has their own
problems in their personal life

00:15:50.640 --> 00:15:52.350
and in their business life.

00:15:52.350 --> 00:15:54.620
And sometimes the
company you work for--

00:15:54.620 --> 00:15:56.640
I mean, you guys
are lucky like I

00:15:56.640 --> 00:15:59.400
was-- in an emerging
field at the time,

00:15:59.400 --> 00:16:01.230
and you're all in
an emerging field.

00:16:01.230 --> 00:16:03.300
But companies go
through ups and Downs,

00:16:03.300 --> 00:16:05.730
and they really are
not worried about you.

00:16:05.730 --> 00:16:08.520
And so it's really about
changing your mindset

00:16:08.520 --> 00:16:13.770
from a victim and thinking that
any job is good or bad to I

00:16:13.770 --> 00:16:16.590
have to make whatever
job I have under whatever

00:16:16.590 --> 00:16:20.010
circumstances a lesson,
a learning lesson

00:16:20.010 --> 00:16:22.400
to this puzzle that is my life.

00:16:22.400 --> 00:16:24.780
That little by little,
all the puzzle pieces

00:16:24.780 --> 00:16:27.930
are going to make sense because
you are on a journey that's

00:16:27.930 --> 00:16:31.410
going to take you somewhere
where all the puzzle pieces are

00:16:31.410 --> 00:16:32.655
going to come in handy.

00:16:32.655 --> 00:16:34.530
SPEAKER 1: Now, speaking
of changing mindset,

00:16:34.530 --> 00:16:37.470
so one thing that I really
related to in your book

00:16:37.470 --> 00:16:40.800
was the notion of our
relationship with fear

00:16:40.800 --> 00:16:41.652
and failure.

00:16:41.652 --> 00:16:43.110
Especially as the
Latino community,

00:16:43.110 --> 00:16:46.000
I think we oftentimes
are more risk averse.

00:16:46.000 --> 00:16:48.720
So what can you say
in terms of kind

00:16:48.720 --> 00:16:50.820
of what you've written
in your book, advice

00:16:50.820 --> 00:16:52.660
to us to change that mindset?

00:16:52.660 --> 00:16:55.470
NELY GALAN: So I think
my book, I really

00:16:55.470 --> 00:16:57.996
wanted Latinos to see a Latina--

00:16:57.996 --> 00:16:59.370
and not just
Latinos, everybody--

00:16:59.370 --> 00:17:04.020
to see that a woman of color was
speaking about money and power.

00:17:04.020 --> 00:17:05.460
Very important.

00:17:05.460 --> 00:17:09.060
And that a Latina woman
would say in a book,

00:17:09.060 --> 00:17:10.589
I always wanted to
be a millionaire.

00:17:10.589 --> 00:17:13.319
And not from a place of greed
because, in our culture,

00:17:13.319 --> 00:17:16.470
it's being rich in
every way that matters--

00:17:16.470 --> 00:17:19.210
but from a place
of knowing my power

00:17:19.210 --> 00:17:20.960
and knowing that it's
possible and knowing

00:17:20.960 --> 00:17:22.790
that that's why we came here.

00:17:22.790 --> 00:17:26.270
But what gets in the way of that
for all of us, at least for me,

00:17:26.270 --> 00:17:29.270
fear and fear of failure.

00:17:29.270 --> 00:17:33.930
It happens every day of my life
still, every day of my life.

00:17:33.930 --> 00:17:36.320
So what I say in the
book is that to make it

00:17:36.320 --> 00:17:39.687
to the end of your life you
have to change your relationship

00:17:39.687 --> 00:17:40.520
to fear and failure.

00:17:40.520 --> 00:17:44.060
And for me, I've had to turn
fear and failure into my best

00:17:44.060 --> 00:17:46.190
friends.

00:17:46.190 --> 00:17:50.096
Fear shows up every day,
and it's not a real thing.

00:17:50.096 --> 00:17:50.720
It's a feeling.

00:17:50.720 --> 00:17:54.290
And what comes up for all of
us, which is human, is run away,

00:17:54.290 --> 00:17:54.950
run away.

00:17:54.950 --> 00:17:55.460
Go away.

00:17:55.460 --> 00:17:56.410
Don't do it.

00:17:56.410 --> 00:17:58.970
And for me-- and all of
you in the tech world--

00:17:58.970 --> 00:18:03.800
know that a brain, just like
a computer, can be rewired.

00:18:03.800 --> 00:18:05.670
You have to rewire your brain.

00:18:05.670 --> 00:18:08.950
You have to tell yourself, like
I tell myself every day, OK,

00:18:08.950 --> 00:18:09.630
fear shows up--

00:18:09.630 --> 00:18:11.370
I call her a she.

00:18:11.370 --> 00:18:14.660
And I go, OK, you're
telling me I have to do it.

00:18:14.660 --> 00:18:17.330
Do it, do it, do it anyway.

00:18:17.330 --> 00:18:19.280
When my book was
coming out, my dream

00:18:19.280 --> 00:18:22.580
was to have Suzy Orman write
the foreword to my book.

00:18:22.580 --> 00:18:24.270
As a woman of color,
the only person

00:18:24.270 --> 00:18:27.950
I'd ever hear as a woman talk
about money was Suzy Orman.

00:18:27.950 --> 00:18:29.780
I was obsessed with her.

00:18:29.780 --> 00:18:31.670
And I wrote her
this magical email.

00:18:31.670 --> 00:18:32.550
I barely knew her.

00:18:32.550 --> 00:18:35.480
I met her three times, but she
wasn't my friend or anything.

00:18:35.480 --> 00:18:37.580
I wrote her a magical email.

00:18:37.580 --> 00:18:41.716
And I was ready to send it, and
my low self-esteem showed up.

00:18:41.716 --> 00:18:44.000
[SPEAKING SPANISH] Who
do you think you are?

00:18:44.000 --> 00:18:47.210
Like, la Suzy doesn't
have time for you.

00:18:47.210 --> 00:18:50.060
And I was like, do it anyway
because I've wired my brain.

00:18:50.060 --> 00:18:53.220
I say it to myself every day, do
it anyway, do it anyway, do it

00:18:53.220 --> 00:18:53.720
anyway.

00:18:53.720 --> 00:18:56.000
And I went click, send.

00:18:56.000 --> 00:19:00.260
And five minutes later,
Suzy said yes, I'll do it.

00:19:00.260 --> 00:19:02.060
Now, that doesn't always happen.

00:19:02.060 --> 00:19:05.360
But if you don't do it anyway,
maybe 50% chance it'll happen,

00:19:05.360 --> 00:19:06.736
50% it won't.

00:19:06.736 --> 00:19:08.360
But you've got to
keep doing it anyway.

00:19:08.360 --> 00:19:11.690
And then my other thing
was, in our culture,

00:19:11.690 --> 00:19:16.040
failing is like the worst, which
we know in Silicon Valley it's

00:19:16.040 --> 00:19:17.130
like high five.

00:19:17.130 --> 00:19:17.970
Fail!

00:19:17.970 --> 00:19:19.570
High five, next.

00:19:19.570 --> 00:19:22.280
You're around the
corner from the answer.

00:19:22.280 --> 00:19:24.000
But we're not raised like that.

00:19:24.000 --> 00:19:26.640
So my other biggest fear
was fear of failure.

00:19:26.640 --> 00:19:27.650
And I have failed.

00:19:27.650 --> 00:19:31.310
If I showed you my failure tape,
we'd all be crying right now.

00:19:31.310 --> 00:19:33.470
I have failed thousands
and thousands of times.

00:19:33.470 --> 00:19:36.149
To win three times in
your life, you better

00:19:36.149 --> 00:19:37.940
be failing thousands
of times or you're not

00:19:37.940 --> 00:19:39.350
going to win three times.

00:19:39.350 --> 00:19:41.690
And that's all
anybody remembers.

00:19:41.690 --> 00:19:44.270
So how did I rewire my
brain around failure

00:19:44.270 --> 00:19:47.120
when I failed so many
times in my personal life,

00:19:47.120 --> 00:19:50.050
in my business life,
in my financial-- fail?

00:19:50.050 --> 00:19:52.300
I've had to say to
myself, OK, cry it out.

00:19:52.300 --> 00:19:53.080
Cry it out.

00:19:53.080 --> 00:19:54.340
Go mourn.

00:19:54.340 --> 00:19:55.840
And then get back on the horse.

00:19:55.840 --> 00:19:57.070
Get back on the horse.

00:19:57.070 --> 00:19:58.330
Get back on the horse.

00:19:58.330 --> 00:20:00.880
Because if I don't
pull myself out of it,

00:20:00.880 --> 00:20:03.730
around the corner from
my greatest failures

00:20:03.730 --> 00:20:05.560
have been my greatest successes.

00:20:05.560 --> 00:20:09.270
And if I didn't wait, it
wouldn't have happened.

00:20:09.270 --> 00:20:10.760
So that's very important.

00:20:10.760 --> 00:20:11.426
SPEAKER 1: Yeah.

00:20:11.426 --> 00:20:13.470
I think oftentimes
I've even faced that.

00:20:13.470 --> 00:20:16.580
I call it the imposter
syndrome that we

00:20:16.580 --> 00:20:18.800
bring with us like in
our everyday lives,

00:20:18.800 --> 00:20:21.500
us questioning if
we should be here.

00:20:21.500 --> 00:20:23.130
Especially in the
tech industry, there

00:20:23.130 --> 00:20:25.160
is this large
conversation that we all

00:20:25.160 --> 00:20:28.560
hear every day around diversity
and the lack of diversity.

00:20:28.560 --> 00:20:30.560
And so us killing the
imposter syndrome,

00:20:30.560 --> 00:20:33.930
and I've also said I leave
that girl out the door.

00:20:33.930 --> 00:20:36.530
NELY GALAN: Well, let's talk
about that, that diversity

00:20:36.530 --> 00:20:39.920
and imposter syndrome because
I feel like the diversity

00:20:39.920 --> 00:20:44.170
is such a hot potato, and I
think we need to blow it up.

00:20:44.170 --> 00:20:46.262
Because diversity,
to me, the way--

00:20:46.262 --> 00:20:47.720
and especially,
I'm older than you,

00:20:47.720 --> 00:20:51.060
so I grew up in a whole
other world of diversity--

00:20:51.060 --> 00:20:55.590
I think diversity means
somebody is doing us a favor.

00:20:55.590 --> 00:20:58.340
And I think we need to
like blow that thing up

00:20:58.340 --> 00:21:03.020
because the truth of the matter
is, multicultural people are

00:21:03.020 --> 00:21:07.790
about to become the majority in
this country by the year 2022.

00:21:07.790 --> 00:21:11.630
Number two, when multicultural
women are the number one

00:21:11.630 --> 00:21:14.720
consumer in America,
the answer is

00:21:14.720 --> 00:21:16.460
we're doing everybody
else a favor.

00:21:16.460 --> 00:21:19.580
And if the company doesn't
look like all of us,

00:21:19.580 --> 00:21:22.700
it will sooner or
later fail because that

00:21:22.700 --> 00:21:26.630
means you have no relationship
to your customer, the number

00:21:26.630 --> 00:21:28.720
one customer in the world.

00:21:28.720 --> 00:21:29.420
Period.

00:21:29.420 --> 00:21:32.010
So you really have
to take that in.

00:21:32.010 --> 00:21:35.120
So somehow, we've told ourselves
a story about diversity.

00:21:35.120 --> 00:21:40.070
Blow that word up
because they are

00:21:40.070 --> 00:21:43.700
lucky to have us because we
represent their number one

00:21:43.700 --> 00:21:44.370
customer.

00:21:44.370 --> 00:21:47.640
So let's not ever
think that again.

00:21:47.640 --> 00:21:48.530
SPEAKER 1: I love it.

00:21:48.530 --> 00:21:50.300
Now, how is it that
you-- in your book,

00:21:50.300 --> 00:21:53.340
you talk about in order
for you to be chosen you

00:21:53.340 --> 00:21:54.590
have to choose yourself first.

00:21:54.590 --> 00:21:55.220
NELY GALAN: That's right.

00:21:55.220 --> 00:21:56.530
SPEAKER 1: How do
you go about that?

00:21:56.530 --> 00:21:57.113
Tell us a few.

00:21:57.113 --> 00:21:58.880
NELY GALAN: Well,
if I ask a man--

00:21:58.880 --> 00:22:00.440
as someone who
worked in television,

00:22:00.440 --> 00:22:02.106
has worked in television
for many years,

00:22:02.106 --> 00:22:03.860
I cast a lot of people.

00:22:03.860 --> 00:22:06.980
And let's say I'm
casting a cooking show.

00:22:06.980 --> 00:22:09.266
And I go up to a man and I
say, well, what do you do?

00:22:09.266 --> 00:22:09.890
Oh, I'm a chef.

00:22:09.890 --> 00:22:10.598
I've been a chef.

00:22:10.598 --> 00:22:11.840
I'm an award-winning chef.

00:22:11.840 --> 00:22:14.880
And maybe they just
started six months ago.

00:22:14.880 --> 00:22:18.800
If I say that to a
woman, you guys go,

00:22:18.800 --> 00:22:21.410
oh, I kind of can
cook really well.

00:22:21.410 --> 00:22:23.870
